# Demonstrates: C94 — assignment expressions provably outside the target field range

# These rows lock both C94 message shapes used here.
# The final row is intentionally safe because its interval partially overlaps [0, 100].

precept AssignmentConstraintsDemo

field Score as number default 50 min 0 max 100
field Boost as number default 200 min 200 max 500

state Review initial
state Applied

event AddBoost
event ApplyDrop
event SafeAdjust

# C94: Score + Boost always lands above the field's maximum.
# EXPECT: C94 | severity=error | match=exact | message=Assignment to 'Score' is provably outside the field's constraint range. Expression produces 200 to 600 (inclusive), but field requires 0 to 100 (inclusive). | line=20 | start=39 | end=52
from Review on AddBoost -> set Score = Score + Boost -> transition Applied

# C94: Score - Boost always lands below the field's minimum.
# EXPECT: C94 | severity=error | match=exact | message=Assignment to 'Score' is provably outside the field's constraint range. Expression produces -500 to -100 (inclusive), but field requires 0 to 100 (inclusive). | line=24 | start=40 | end=53
from Review on ApplyDrop -> set Score = Score - Boost -> transition Applied

# SAFE: Score - 60 produces [-10, 40], which partially overlaps [0, 100], so no C94 fires.
from Review on SafeAdjust -> set Score = Score - 60 -> transition Applied
